properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 6 at 4:10AM EST until January 8 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 20 to 25 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and waves 7 to 10 feet occurring. For the
Gale Watch, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt
and waves 6 to 11 feet possible.

* WHERE...Lake Superior from Upper Entrance to Portage Canal to
Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian Border.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 11 AM EST this morning. For
the Gale Watch, from late tonight through Wednesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
